# Auto-Attack Logic Integration Walkthrough

We have successfully integrated the Auto-Attack logic into the ArtaleAI path planning system.

## Changes Implemented

### 1. Attack Mechanics ([CharacterMovementController.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs))
- Added [PerformAttackAsync(int cooldownMs)](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#605-626) method.
- Sends a `Ctrl` key press to attack.
- Implements a configurable cooldown (currently set to 1000ms).
- Ensures movement is fully stopped before attacking.

### 2. Detection & Trigger Logic ([MainForm.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs))
- **Condition Check**: [CheckAutoAttackCondition()](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#1000-1054) verifies:
    - [Start](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#2687-2751) checkbox is checked.
    - Path, Detection Mode, and Monster Templates are selected.
    - Monsters are detected within the defined **Attack Range**.
- **Execution Flow**:
    - When a monster enters the attack range, [PerformAutoAttackAsync()](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#1055-1090) is triggered.
    - Path Planning movement is immediately paused ([StopMovement()](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#345-365)).
    - Attack key (`Ctrl`) is pressed.
    - System waits for 1 second (Cooldown).
    - Movement automatically resumes in the next frame cycle.

## Verification

### Automated Verification
- **Build Status**: The project compiled successfully with 0 errors.

### Manual Verification Steps
1.  **Configure**:
    - Select a valid Path File.
    - Select a Detection Mode (e.g., Color).
    - Select Monster Templates.
    - Check the [Start](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#2687-2751) box.
2.  **Test**:
    - Observe the character moving along the path.
    - When a monster appears in the **Attack Range Box** (Blue/Green box):
    - **Observe**: Character should stop moving.
    - **Observe**: Character should perform an attack animation (Ctrl key).
    - **Observe**: Logs should show `[自動攻擊] 發現怪物...` and `[自動攻擊] 攻擊完成...`.
    - **Observe**: Character resumes path following after ~1 second.

> [!NOTE]
> The attack logic is designed to prioritize attacking over moving. If multiple monsters keep appearing, the character may stay in place to fight them off before continuing the path.
